name: $url
desc: Returns: An absolute URI that is used to identify this service definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this service definition is (or will be) published. The URL SHOULD include the major version of the service definition. For more information see [Technical and Business Versions](resource.html#versions).

name: $identifier
desc: Returns: A formal identifier that is used to identify this service definition when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This is used for CMS or NQF identifiers for a measure artifact. Note that at least one identifier is required for non-experimental active artifacts.

name: $::version
desc: Returns: The identifier that is used to identify this version of the service definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the service definition author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, it might be a timestamp (e.g. yyyymmdd) if a managed version is not available. There is also no expectation that versions can be placed in a lexicographical sequence.
